------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CALCULATION OF NUMBER OF TURNS
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

In this casee number of turns for both primary and secondery will be similar as it is 1:1 transformer  
  
  Voltage per Turn = K (Q)^0.5
  
                     K = 0.33 (according to ISCODE)  ; Q is the Power (in kVA)
                     
  Number of Turns  = No load Primary Voltage/Voltage per turn
                   = 
                   
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------                   
CALCULATION OF ADDITIONAL NUMBER OF TURNS FOR 5% TAPPING
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
 This 5% tapping is provided to counter the effect of variable no load primary voltage.Since it can vary upto 5% both up and down. Multiply
 0.05 with number of turns to get additional turns which needs to be added with previous number.
 
 Turns Additional : 0.05 x Number of Turns    
 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------                   
AXIAL AND RADIAL LENGTH OF WINDING   
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Axial Length  : (Diameter of Wire  + Anamel coating  + Insulation paper  + Minimum Gap) x Number of Turns
Radial Length :(Diameter of Wire  + Anamel coating  + Insulation paper  + Minimum Gap) x Number of Layers
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
                   
                   
